Subject: SharePoint permissions not accurate
Description:
Hello,
We have recently migrated our on-prem user home directories to OneDrive and I need to create permissions reports for our users. Unfortunately, I am not seeing all subdirectories. I currently see Social, Documents, Form Template and Style Library. How can I see all subdirectories in and their permissions if shared with other users?
What_We_Know__c: Jobs were overlapping causing host resource issues.
Next_Steps__c: Awaiting for the next set of scans complete.
Solution_Comment__c:
Confirmed that the current version of Stealth application(s) running in the Environment:

Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) formally StealthAUDIT (SA) 11.6.0.112

Created the new App-registrations and Cert for the connection: Netwrix Enterprise Auditor v11.6 > Administration > Jobs Tree > Instant Job Wizard > SP_RegisterAzureAppAuth Job
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/EnterpriseAuditor_11.6/page/Content/EnterpriseAuditor/Admin/Jobs/InstantJobs/SP_RegisterAzureAppAuth.htm
Our Tier 2 (Tay) was able to correct my configuration error for this job.

Once this completed and the new Connection Profile was in place and the console was restarted and a Zero level Job was tested.
Zero level scan was Successful.

We shifted the SPO scans to run one after another from the Parent folder >> Jobs >> SharePoint
This will keep the Collection jobs 5-SPAA_BulkImport, 6-SPAC_BulkImport, 7-SPAA_Exceptions, and Reporting from stepping on each other within the SQL DB

Corrected the profile for the SPAC_SystemScans.
